{"by": "jampekka", "id": 43182780, "parent": 43182703, "text": "modReLU seems to just increase the magnitude of the input value, and rotate it to the original polar angle. With clipping off negative magnitudes.<p>Or equivalently rotates a (real) bias term with the input angle and adds that into the original.<p><pre><code>  (abs(z) + c)*exp(i*arg(z)) = abs(z)*exp(i*arg(z)) + c*exp(i*arg(z)) = z + c*exp(i*arg(z))</code></pre>", "time": 1740570084, "type": "comment"}